This gorgeous modern completely newly renovated house has all high end finishings like quartz countertops in the kitchen, stainless steel appliances, full size fridge. Large capacity new washer and dryer located in cupboard right off the kitchen.

From the pictures you will see the stunning and artistically designed tiled bathroom on main floor with hand held shower head. Upstairs bathrooms have rain shower heads.

The main floor living room has an internet-enabled 55" smart tv, with Netflix, free wifi, large electric fireplace, and a couch that pulls out to a queen sofa bed. In the master bedroom upstairs you will also find a 55" TV plus 2nd bedroom has a 42" TV.

Off the living room, the dining area seats six, and the kitchen counter another 4 people on stools. Our kitchen comes with everything you need to cook at home. There are stainless steel appliances -stove, dishwasher, microwave, pots pans, cutlery and some general spices to get you started. 

The three bedrooms each have queen beds with comfy duvets and linens. There are three bathrooms - one on the main floor with a large shower area, and at the top of the stairs with a bath/shower. Plus a large en suite stand up shower off master bedroom

Full size washer & dryer off kitchen

The 21 blocks of Commercial Drive from Venables at the north end, to 13th Avenue at the south, over a mile long, are home to the most eclectic mix of businesses in the city. Of the more than 400 businesses on the Drive, the majority are single location, owner-operated, making the product mix, dining experiences, produce, entertainment and services completely unique.
This neighbourhood repeatedly receives the Georgia Straight Reader's Choice award as the best neighbourhood in the City. We've also been ranked one of the 10 hippest neighbourhoods in North America by Utne Reader. Frequently described as Vancouver's Greenwich Village, or as creative and bohemian as Paris' Rive Gauche
You'll be close to the trendy Commercial Drive, a hot spot for young adults and urban professionals for its great eateries, pubs, and interesting shops. Drug store and liquor store are nearby. 'The Drive' has lots of events during the summer like 'Italian Days' and there's a large park the community gathers in.

There will be 1 parking spot in a driveway with a sliding steal lockable gate. Also an additional steel gate for entering the yard right in front of the main entrance. Unassigned parking is also available across the street.

You are a 3 block walk to Commercial Drive, which has a plethora of coffee shops, restaurants, local boutiques, grocery stores, drug stores, and other amenities etc. 
Bus stops are close by, within a short walking distance. Vancouver has a great transit system. The skytrain is a short bus ride, 5 minute drive, or 25 minute walk. Downtown is a 5 minute drive or a 35 minute walk to (Rogers Arena area or BC Place area of downtown)

Marpole is a thriving residential community on the edge of Vancouver and another hidden gem. Marpole is a vibrant and growing neighborhood in the southern area of Vancouver bordered by Park Drive to the north, Granville Street to the west, Main Street to the east and the Fraser River to the south. This area is actually one of Vancouver's oldest settlements.Features:2020 build a new development of these unique townhouses and offer you a beautiful garden-level townhouse unit in the location that brings you close to everything. Kitsilano Beach, English Bay and North Shore Mountain ViewsLocation: 302 - 2215 York Avenue, Vancouver, BCIf you are looking for an apartment immersed in the area that truly capitalizes on the best of the Kits beach lifestyle that Vancouver has to offer, then you have found it! Scroll down for photos and video.A privately owned, well-maintained and quiet walk-up building in the heart of the Kitsilano Beach community; with one of the shortest walks to the park, beach and water available, you will truly come to enjoy the area ranked as one of Vancouver's Best Places. Discover the perfect blend of mid-century charm and modern comfort at 2215 York Avenue, Vancouver, BC. This one-bedroom, one-bathroom apartment in the heart of Kitsilano offers a cozy living space and an ideal location for those seeking a balanced, urban lifestyle.Enjoy the convenience of heat and hot water included in the rent. This three-story walk-up building, constructed in the 1960s, retains some of its original charm, providing a unique character that distinguishes it from the contemporary buildings in the area.The interior features hardwood floors and a welcoming living area that extends to a very spacious private rooftop deck, where you can take in the partially obstructed views of Kitsilano Beach, the ocean, and the North Shore Mountains. Additionally, the sizable bedroom boasts a pie-shaped balcony, providing you with not one, but two outdoor spaces to enjoy the fresh air.The building is equipped with coin-operated laundry facilities, ensuring you have the convenience of doing laundry without having to leave the premises.The vibrant Kitsilano neighbourhood is known for its picturesque surroundings and active community. Just a short walk away, you'll find the stunning Kitsilano Beach, perfect for sunbathing, swimming, or engaging in various watersports. For those who love to explore, the scenic Seawall offers a peaceful walk or bike ride along the waterfront.Living in this area means having access to a plethora of trendy boutiques, fitness studios, and diverse dining options. Indulge in the local culinary scene, from farm-to-table eateries to global cuisine, at the many bars, cafes, and restaurants nearby.Outdoor enthusiasts will appreciate the apartment's proximity to both the mountains and the ocean. Hiking and mountain biking trails are just a short drive away, and the nearby ski resorts offer a winter playground. For a more urban experience, the city's best shopping, arts, and cultural venues are easily accessible via public transportation or a short car ride.Embrace the charm and convenience of coastal living at 2215 York Avenue in Kitsilano.500 sqft Apartment Unit: One large Bedroom, One Bathroom, Top-Floor.The property features bicycle storage in the secured garage, and on-site coin-op laundry, with central heating and hot water included in the rental price.
